File_Description: Data package level readme. Contains data package summary; acknowledgements; and contact information.
Data dictionary that defines columns headers across all comma-separated values (CSV) files contained in the data package.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: File-level metadata that lists and describes all of the files contained in the data package.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021); ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for File-level Metadata (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Wrapper script that launches container for using the Generic Mapping Tools and executes plotting script in container.
Figure created by corresponding plotting notebook or script. The asterisk (*) indicates the figure number followed by a brief description of the figure.

Figure plotting script for Bash shell that plots the corresponding figure. Many scripts here use the Generic Mapping Tools (GMT) and as long as Docker is installed; you can launch these scripts with the fig_gmt_plot.sh wrapper. The asterisk (*) indicates the figure number followed by a brief description of the figure.

Figure plotting Jupyter notebook or very last stages data post-processing notebook to create intermediate results for corresponding figure. The asterisk (*) indicates the figure number followed by a brief description of the figure.

YAML format Conda environment definition file for reconstructing Conda environment and Python packages used for the corresponding figure generation/postprocessing notebooks. This file is compressed (i.e. a binary) to avoid GitHub printing security warnings in case there are old packages. The asterisk (*) indicates the figure number followed by a brief description of the figure.

Compressed comma-separated values (CSV) file containing predictions at all RiverAtlas segments in the 7411 and 7412 Marsden square tiles. The asterisk (*) indicates which machine learning (ML) model in the branch. This file is compressed due to its large size and stored as an important intermediate result because these predictions take more than 45GB of RAM and 10 minutes to run.
Compressed GMT .xyz segment delimited file for the RiverAtlas data in the 7411 Marsden Square. This file is compressed due to its large size.
Compressed GMT .xyz segment delimited file for the RiverAtlas data in the 7412 Marsden Square. This file is compressed due to its large size.
Python script implementing a simple last-ditch attempt to recover missing oxygen values by converting dissolved oxygen (O2) to dissolved oxygen percent saturation (O2%sat) or O2%sat to O2.
Instructions for how to use the plotting scripts/notebooks.

Table for manuscript created by fig04-05-06-machine learning (ML)-results.ipynb using the data dictionaries in the same directory. Feature permutation index (FPI) importance scores are from the feature permutation index (FPI) results from the machine learning (ML) model from the branch name that is indicated by the asterisk (*).
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Data dictionary that defines columns headers across all comma-separated values (CSV) files from RiverAtlas data.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: RiverAtlas data at GLORICH (GLObal RIver Chemistry Database) sites along with limited GLORICH insitu chemistry data for making predictions at all GLORICH sites.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Machine learning (ML) model predictions at the GLORICH (GLObal RIver Chemistry Database) sites using RiverAtlas and GLORICH data. The asterisk (*) indicates the machine learning (ML) model in the branch.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: List of the top features/variables resulting from the feature permutation index (FPI) analysis. The asterisk (*) indicates the machine learning (ML) model in the branch.

RiverAtlas data at WHONDRS (Worldwide Hydrobiogeochemistry Observation Network for Dynamic River Systems) sites long with limited WHONDRS site metadata for cross checking that the data colocation process works as expected for variables that overlap between the two data sets.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Predictions of respiration rate at the WHONDRS (Worldwide Hydrobiogeochemistry Observation Network for Dynamic River Systems) sites made with the machine learning (ML) model ensemble. The asterisk (*) indicates the branch.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: WHONDRS (Worldwide Hydrobiogeochemistry Observation Network for Dynamic River Systems) data in machine learning (ML)-ready format (i.e. unranked classes converted to 1hot data; ranked classes converted to integer scale; all features/inputs merged by Sample_ID).
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Data dictionary that defines columns headers across all comma-separated values (CSV) files contained in the published CM data package with the addition of WHONDRS (Worldwide Hydrobiogeochemistry Observation Network for Dynamic River Systems) Fourier-transform ion cyclotron resonance (FTICR) data dictionary entries and custom machine learning (ML) model features created by the code in this repository.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Main input file for machine learning (ML) workflow. In some cases this file is identical to WHONDRS_S19S_SSS_merged.csv.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Output of the 4th preprocessing step (collocating the prediction data with the RiverAtlas database).

File_Description: Script that runs the 6th and final step of preprocessing which merges physical (RiverAtlas) data with chemical data (WHONDRS (Worldwide Hydrobiogeochemistry Observation Network for Dynamic River Systems)). Step 5 is internal to the main preprocessing orchestration script.
Output of the 6th preprocessing step contains the final predict data set.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Output of the 6th preprocessing step contains the site ID and latitude/longitude coordinates of each site for geolocation later. Site ID and latitude/longitude are not used to train the machine learning (ML) models and so they must be kept separate.
Output of the 6th preprocessing step contains the final training (i.e. observed) data set.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Output of the 6th preprocessing step contains the site ID and latitude/longitude coordinates of each site for geolocation later. Site ID and latitude/longitude are not used to train the machine learning (ML) models and so they must be kept separate.
Script that orchestrates all the preprocessing steps prior to training the machine learning (ML) models in the machine learning (ML) workflow.
Compressed file with polygon outline for the contiguous United States (CONUS) region used for selecting points within CONUS.
